                            <comment id="13445474" author="eli" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 00:04:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good, minor nits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&quot;-Dsnappy.prefix or -Dsnappy.lib&quot; should be &quot;and&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&quot;if Snappy is missing&quot; should be  &quot;and snappy is not installed on your host&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&quot;Most of the time, these options should not be necessary&quot; should be something like &quot;These options are not required if the snappy libraries and headers are installed in the system lib and includes directories.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13445518" author="cmccabe" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 00:40:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I reworded this a bit.  Thinking about it, I realized the snappy options might look better in a single section.  Also there should be some intro text about what the heck snappy is before launching into these details.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;-Dsnappy.prefix or -Dsnappy.lib&quot; should be &quot;and&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Seemed better to give each option its own section, I got rid of the &apos;or&apos; completely...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;Most of the time, these options should not be necessary&quot; should be something like &quot;These options are not required if the snappy libraries and headers are installed in the system lib and includes directories.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I replaced this with &quot;You do not need this option if you have installed snappy through... a package manager&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
